{"lemma":"مُفَصَّلٌ","slug":"مُفَصَّلٌ","root":"ف.ص.ل","root_slug":"ف-ص-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ص-ل","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُفَصَّل","root":"فصل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34011"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"knuckle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"skeletal joint"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"detailed"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Noun of place from the root ف ص ل (f ṣ l), with the noun itself forming the denominal root م ف ص ل (m f ṣ l), whence تَمَفْصَلَ (tamafṣala, “to connect as joints; to form a joint”), among others, derives.\n\nDerived from the passive participle of فَصَّلَ (faṣṣala, “to detail”)."},"ipa":["/mu.fasˤ.sˤal/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34011","headword_ar":"مَفْصِلٌ","root":"fSl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any place of meeting"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"juncture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place of separation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of two bones of the body and limbs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"members;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSolN","text_ar":"فَصْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single one of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafaASil","text_ar":"مَفَاصِل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the limbs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"members:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a joint such as the elbow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knee"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knuckle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a joint as meaning a bone having an articulation at each end,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at one end, together with the flesh that is upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in a trad. in which it is said that the mulct for any"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoSil","text_ar":"مَفْصِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a human being is the third of the mulct for the [whole] finger, it means the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoSil","text_ar":"مَفْصِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any of the fingers or toes; i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion between any"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anomalataAni","text_ar":"اَنْمَلَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two knuckles;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is a loose and an imperfect explanation; for to it should be added, and also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ungual portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion in which is the nail;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the word is here applied to denote"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any of the phalanges with the flesh that is upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the T &c., in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nml","text_ar":"نمل"},{"kind":"text","text":", one of the explanations of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^anomalapu","text_ar":"الاَنْمَلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is “ the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoSil","text_ar":"مَفْصِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"in which is the nail ”]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And [hence] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA^otiyka biAlA^amori mino mafoSilihi","text_ar":"يَاْتِيكَ بِالاَمْرِ مِنْ مَفْصِلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He will tell thee the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"tracing it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the point on which it turns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hinges;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(like as one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino faS~ihi","text_ar":"مِنْ فَصِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.;) or],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its utmost point"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"particular,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munotahaAhu","text_ar":"مُنْتَهَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [This saying may be originally a hemistich, thus:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wayaA^otiyka biAlA^amori mino mafoSiliho"},{"kind":"text","text":"like the similar saying ending with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faS~ihi","text_ar":"فَصِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  In the following saying of Aboo-Dhu-eyb, [the former half of which I give from art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tfl","text_ar":"طفل"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the S, the latter half only being cited in the present art. in the S and M and O,]"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waA_in~a HadiyvFA minoki lawo tabo*uliynahu\n                      \n                     \n                        janaY Aln~aHoli fiY A^alobaAni Euw*K maTaAfili\n                      \n                     \n                        maTaAfiyla A^abokaArK HadiyvK nitaAjuhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        tu$aAbu bimaA='K mivoli maA='i AlmafaASili"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And verily discourse from thee, if thou wouldst bestow it, would be"},{"kind":"text","text":"(like)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gathered honey of bees in the milk"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milks"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"camels"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as have recently brought forth, having young ones with them, such as have young ones with them"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that have brought forth but once, whose bringing forth has been recent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"such milk being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mixed with water like the water of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mfASl","text_ar":"مفاصل"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmafaASil","text_ar":"المَفَاصِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoSilN","text_ar":"مَفْصِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, O) signifies (accord. to As, S, O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place of separation"},{"kind":"text","text":"(↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munofaSal","text_ar":"مُنْفَصَل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the mountain from the tract of sand, these two having between them crushed and small pebbles, so that the water thereof is clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and glistens,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayaboruqu","text_ar":"وَيَبْرُقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and is shallow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayariq~u","text_ar":"وَيَرِقُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) the poet meaning to describe the clearness of the water because of its descending from the mountain and not passing by dust nor earth: (M:) or it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard stones"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compactly disposed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heaped up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K: in the former,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaraASifap","text_ar":"مُتَرَاصِفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the latter,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaraAkimap","text_ar":"مُتَرَاكِمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and (M, K) it is said to signify (M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is between two mountains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of sand and crushed pebbles, the water whereof is clear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or, accord. to AO,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the water-courses"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a valley: (O:) accord. to Abu-l-'Omeythil,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the clefts in mountains, from which water flows;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and only said of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what are between two mountains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the T, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoSil","text_ar":"مَفْصِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any place, in a mountain, upon which the sun does not rise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and it is said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='u AlmafaASili","text_ar":"مَا=ءُ المَفَاصِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what flows from between the two joints"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino bayoni AlmafoSilayoni","text_ar":"مِنْ بَيْنِ المَفْصِلَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when one of them is cut from the other; like clear water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoSilN","text_ar":"مَفْصِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) AA says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mfASl","text_ar":"مفاصل"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the verse are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mfASl","text_ar":"مفاصل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bones;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and that it likens that water to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA='","text_ar":"ما=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the flesh: (O, TA:) and IAar says the like thereof. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","O","Msb","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}